wp.me\/p95VHY-9RZ","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":33792,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/11\/20\/hasan-never-forgot-his-sins\/","url_meta":{"origin":37943,"position":0},"title":"Hasan on Fear: He enters Paradise because he never forgot his sins","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 20, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Hisham ibn Hassan reported: Al-Hasan al-Basri, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cVerily, a man may commit a sin and he never forgets it, always fearing it, until he enters Paradise.\u201d Source: al-Zuhd li-Ah\u0323mad ibn H\u0323anbal 1581 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0647\u0650\u0634\u064e\u0627\u0645 \u0628\u0652\u0646 \u062d\u064e\u0633\u0651\u064e\u0627\u0646 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0633\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0635\u0631\u064a \u0631\u062d\u0645\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0625\u0650\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0631\u0651\u064e\u062c\u064f\u0644\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":35522,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/04\/04\/umar-all-deeds-sincere\/","url_meta":{"origin":37943,"position":1},"title":"Umar on Ikhlaas: Make all my deeds sincere for Your sake","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 4, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Hasan reported: Umar, may Allah be pleased with him, used to say, \u201cO Allah, make my deeds righteous, make them purely for Your sake, and do not let anyone else have a share of them.\u201d Source: al-Zuhd li-Ah\u0323mad ibn H\u0323anbal 617 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u062d\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0631\u064e \u0631\u0636\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0639\u0646\u0647 \u0643\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u064a\u064e\u0642\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25284,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/10\/17\/mutarrif-humble-regret-worship\/","url_meta":{"origin":37943,"position":2},"title":"Mutarrif on Worship: Humble regret better than arrogant worship","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 17, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Ahmad reported: Mutarrif, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \"That I spend the night sleeping and awaken regretful is more beloved to me than to spend the night standing in prayer and awaken impressed with myself.\" Source: al-Zuhd li-Ah\u0323mad Ibn H\u0323anbal 1357 \u0639\u0646 \u0623\u062d\u0645\u062f \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0645\u064f\u0637\u064e\u0631\u0651\u0650\u0641\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u062d\u0645\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":35053,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/01\/25\/good-dunya-akhirah\/","url_meta":{"origin":37943,"position":3},"title":"Hasan on Dua: Goodness is knowledge in world, Paradise in Hereafter","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 25, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Hisham ibn Hassan reported: Al-Hasan, may Allah have mercy on him, said in regards to His saying, \u201cO Lord, give us good in the world and good in the Hereafter,\u201d (2:201) that good in the world is knowledge and worship, and good in the Hereafter is Paradise. Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":24793,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/05\/11\/wahb-beware-lowly-hawa\/","url_meta":{"origin":37943,"position":4},"title":"Wahb on Arrogance: Beware of lowly desires, evil friends, selfish pride","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 11, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Ahmad reported: Wahb ibn Munnabih, may Allah have mercy on him, delivered a sermon to the people upon the pulpit, and he said, \u201cGuard for me three things. Beware of whims that are followed, an evil companion, and the vanity of a man impressed by his own opinion.\u201d Source: al-Zuhd\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":20860,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2015\/09\/01\/hasan-everyday-obey-eid\/","url_meta":{"origin":37943,"position":5},"title":"Hasan on Eid: Every day Muslims obey Allah a celebration","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 1, 2015","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Rajab reported: Hasan al-Basri, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cEvery day in which Allah is not disobeyed is a celebration. Every day the believer spends in obedience, servitude, remembrance, and gratitude is a celebration.\u201d Source: Lat\u0323a\u0304'if al-Ma'a\u0304rif 1\/278 \u0639\u0646 \u0627\u0628\u0646 \u0631\u062c\u0628 \u0642\u0627\u0644 \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0633\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0635\u0631\u064a \u0631\u062d\u0645\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u062a\u0639\u0627\u0644\u0649\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/37943","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=37943"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/37943\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=37943"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=37943"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=37943"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}